review_blob: IPA share with some friends. Love the forward malt with the balance of the hops. Straying from my typical West Coast style IPA but I really enjoyed this one!
Boom! Hopsplosion in my face! Big citrus aromatics, lighter body and leans in the hop direction. Love this!
Bright, tart, great aroma. Everything I want and expect in a Berlinerweisse. And it comes in cans to boot. Awesome!
beer_name: Destihl Wild Sour Series: Counter ClockWeisse

review_blob: Great aroma! Belgian yeast, fresh berries, stone fruit. Full body and well rounded. Dry finish, no cloying sweetness. Really delicious beer!
Absolutely one of my favorite beers in the World! Every flavor in this beer stands out and shines but not over-done. I cant wait to pick up another case!
A dry saison is my desert Island beer so Im really partial to this one. Bottle pour, golden in color. Citrus, earthy aroma. Dry, crisp, high carbonation. Absolutely delicious!

Huge Piney Hops in the aroma. Alcohol is incredibly well hidden, I didnt realize the percentage at first. Body is smooth, crisp and dry. Super delicious beer and one of my favorites so far this Season!
beer_name: Black Market Holiday 2014-2015 (Triple Black Rye IPA)

review_blob: Enjoyed this last night with a couple friends. This is one of the best Imperial IPAs Ive had from Washington. Alcohol melds well, hop aroma is amazing and the body really helps showcase the hops. Big fan of this brewery!

Had this yesterday for the first time! Super excited to find this at my local bottle shop. I drink this every chance I get in OR. Super amazing hop aroma, lighter body to showcase the hops. True West Coast IPA. Love it!

Wonderful cinnamon and chocolate on the nose. Smooth drinking Winter Ale with just a touch a spice, nothing overwhelming. Perfect for sitting down with on those cold winter evenings. Definitely one for the holiday seasons!
Another amazing offering from this brewery! Love the apple juice, delicious fruit character and a nice tartness like a cider. Super excited about the Dealers Choice Series so far!
Oh my! Deliciousness! Relatively still cider with classic Spanish Sidra characters. Great acidity, wonderful balance. Truly expresses the apple. Cant go wrong!

Just like the rest of their ciders, this one is outstanding. Sour cider with strawberry and rhubarb. A classic pairing in a very unique cider. This is one of my favorite releases from these guys. World Class cider makers!

Great example of the style. You dont get a lot of Biere de Gardes anymore and this is definitely my favorite one. The combination of spices present a wonderful aroma that complements the malt character.
Excellent, full bodied saison. Refreshing, gentle acidity, rustic aroma. Everything I love in a Belgian-style saison.

Rum for days in this bad boy. Popped a bottle with a friend recently after giving it some time. Definitely has mellowed from the booziness. I really liked this beer when I first had it and I love it now. Glad Im sitting on a couple bottles.
The fruit in here is outstanding! The acidity is very well balanced with the fruit and barrel character. I would buy this again if I ever see it. Wonderful!
Had on draft. Very refreshing! Loved the color of this as well from the Blueberries. Definitely would drink again and even buy bottles of they have em.
I really enjoyed this cider. It was easy drinking, dry, affordable and in a 16oz can. Everything I wanted!

I dont drink a lot of fruited ciders but this one is amazing! Big fruit nose. Full body, fruity but doesnt finish sweet. Effervescent, carbonation complements sweetness from the fruit. Definitely a home run! Love the color!

Oh. My. Word. I saved a bottle of this from last year and its still so amazing. Orange peel, coriander, cinnamon, nutmeg. So many glorious spices in my nose and mouth. This is my favorite seasonal cider of all time. The 14% ABV isnt a terrible thing either, perfect for cold days. Looking forward to the next release!
Love how effervescent this one is! Also the dryness is amazing, its a nearly perfect cider for me. Could definitely drink all the time. Its Organic to boot!
Rustic, dry, funky, earthy. Reminded me a bit of a Spanish Sidra without too much acidity. Love the wild fermentation aspect of it.
Love everything from these guys. Delicious single-varietal cider. Juicy, dry, crisp, effervescent, refreshing. Epitome of a table cider for me. Loved it!
Sat on this beer for some time and pulled out to enjoy with friends. This is how I love my saisons. Dry, rustic, earthy, dusty, subtle malt sweetness. And who doesnt love MItch Hedberg!

Pulled from my cellar. Im really excited about how this beer has come along. First had it when it was initially released. I like it then, I love it now. Dry, funky, earthy. The Brett has taken this beer great places! I have one left and actually hoping to track down a few more.
Big, bold, hoppy Red ale! The aroma on this beer is outstanding with lots of citrus and malt goodness. The type of beer I always want around in my fridge.
I can see why this won Gold at GABF! Delicious Pale Ale with a phenomenal hop aroma, light body and ABV. Citrus in the nose, with some fruity yeast characters. Big fan and I could drink this all day!
Another great sour from these guys! Great body, complementing acidity, nose is of dry, Belgian saison yeast in the best way. Really hope to find more of this!
Had this on draft. Gentle acidity, complementing malt backbone. Great aroma. Not my favorite Oud Bruin, but not far from the top of the list!
Glad I got my hands on a couple of these. Awesome sour ale! Aroma is acidic, funky, subtle sweetness, barrel, hints of stone fruit. Really a great sour beer!
beer_name: Grand Teton Brewers Series No. 1 - American Sour Aged In Oak Barrels

review_blob: One of my new favorite beers! Big, roasty, rich, but not overly sweet. The aroma is the same. Something Im going to get plenty of to lay down in the cellar!
beer_name: Grand Teton Black Cauldron Imperial Stout

review_blob: Had this on draft. Wasnt sure what to expect from an "Extra Special Brown" but I really liked this. Excellent malt profile, hop aroma was minimal and had a pleasant bitterness in the finish. Definitely something I cold drink pints and pints of.

Everything I expect in a Belgian Tripel. Great Belgian yeast character in the nose, full bodied, finishes medium-dry. Alcohol is spot on for the style. Enjoyed a 12oz bottle of this and will go back for more.

Big, bold, and oaky! Wow did I love this beer! Oxidation in the hops from barrel-aging, but not off putting at all. Everything really complemented the beer. Lots and lots of oak! Its like smelling the inside of an oak barrel. Love it!

Excellent Belgian Quad with a twist. The honey was great, not overwhelming, didnt make it too sweet. Reminded me of fresh honeycomb. Belgian yeast character was spot on for the style. Will definitely drink again.
Great hop aroma, balanced malt profile. I enjoyed this on a nice sunny day and loved the fact its in 12oz bottles!

Batch #8. Aged 4 years in the barrels. Wow! This was an amazing roller coaster for my palate. Oak, honey, whiskey, malt, sherry, stone fruit. Nothing over the top and all the flavors blended well together, wasnt messy at all. I would happily share another bottle with friends again!

Had after I had Kurts Apple Pie. I thought that was going to be the all time winner for me, but this knocked it out of the park. The Whiskey on this is perfect. Exactly what I was hoping for. Smooth, not overly sweet, wonderful aroma! Will have more soon for my cellar!
This changed my mind about mead. Vanilla and spices on the nose, wonderful body. Not cloyingly sweet at all. Very smooth mouthfeel and drinks way too easy for the ABV. Im hooked!
The Strawberry and Rhubarb in this are amazing. They lend a gentle acidity that really complements the sweetness of the honey. I will be getting more of this!
Oh my that is lovely. Melon, apricots, subtle honey. The aroma is wonderful, expressing lots of gentle fruit. This is perfect for an after dinner beverage.
Great ginger aroma! The Blueberry honey compliments the body of the cider, but doesnt add very much sweetness. Acidity is great. Rustic, earthy, very very delicious!
Amazing! Semi-sweet, soft tannins, full, juicy body, dry finish. Aroma is of standing in the middle of an orchard and taking a deep breath. A perfect cider.
I know this cider as Prohibition, but its amazing by any name. Rum, molasses, oak, whiskey, rich, juicy apples. Ive never experienced a cider like this. Truly a unique, mind blowing cider.
beer_name: Sea Cider Rumrunner (2009+ Newfoundland Screech Rum)

review_blob: Hands down my favorite cider in the World. Juicy body, dry finish, very proscecco-like. Tight carbonation. Aroma of juicy delicious apples. I could live on this stuff.
Love this cider! Complex, rustic cider. Great body, tannic mouthfeel, the aroma is amazing. Big fan of Alpenfire!

This beer took me by surprise! Im usually not much of a Pumpkin beer drinker but it was all my friend had at the time. Glad he didnt have anything else! Amber in color, malt forward, smooth body. Spice are present but not overwhelming. Delicious Pumpkin beer for a non-pumpkin beer drinker!

Not only the best Gluten Free beer Ive ever had, but one of the better Belgian Tripels available. Was poured for me by a friend and I wasnt told it was gluten free. I really enjoyed it and then loved it even more when I was told it contained no gluten. Great beer!

Everything I want in a Belgian Quad. Aroma is spot on, body and flavor are what I love in traditional examples of the style. Definitely one of the best domestic representations of the style Ive ever had.
